modules.description: Splits OCaml toplevel sessions into structured chunks containing code phrases and associated expect tests, and parses these chunks into a format that separates OCaml code, expect test outputs, and org-mode markup. Works with strings representing toplevel session content and extracts distinct elements based on syntax markers. Used to convert test files into structured documentation format by isolating code, outputs, and markup sections.

Parses toplevel OCaml code into structured chunks containing expectations, code, and organizational blocks, extracting expectations from %%expect statements and grouping code into contiguous phrases. Works with toplevel_phrase lists, position metadata, and custom types like chunk and mlt_block to represent parsed elements. Processes raw source strings to generate labeled blocks for testing and documentation, separating code, expectations, and org blocks while ignoring comments and irrelevant syntax.
